Heat the oil in a small frying pan and saut√© the red pepper for 6-8 minutes or until soft.Add the garlic and fry for one minute. Stir in the honey then put the mixture into a blender or food processor and liquidise until smooth. Strain through a sieve and cool.For the lamb, drizzle the lamb steak with oil and sprinkle over the paprika and chilli flakes.Heat a griddle pan until hot, then fry the steak for 4-5 minutes on each side or until cooked as desired.  Rest for five minutes.Arrange the herbs on a plate and drizzle the dressing around the edge. Serve with the lamb steak.